{"title_page": "Santa B\u00e1rbara (Ribeira Grande)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = RGR-sbarbara.png\n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]]\n| municipality            = [[Ribeira Grande, Azores|Ribeira Grande]]\n| coordinates             = {{coord|37|47|58|N|25|32|1|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: c. 1522<br>Parish: 10 April 1736<br>Civil parish: June 1971\n| area_total_km2          = 12.84\n| elevation_m             = 88\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 1275\n| postal_code             = 9600-420\n| area_code               = 292\n| patron                  = [[Blessed Virgin Mary|Nossa Senhora das Vit\u00f3rias]]\n| website                 = {{url|http://freguesiasantabarbara.pt/}}\n}}\n'''Santa B\u00e1rbara ''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] for [[Saint Barbara]]) is a parish in the municipality of [[Ribeira Grande, S\u00e3o Miguel|Ribeira Grande]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 1,275,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 12.84&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> It contains the localities Chavinha, Courela, Diogo and Santa B\u00e1rbara.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santa Barbara (Ribeira Grande)}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Ribeira Grande, Azores]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_caption    