{"title_page": "Santa B\u00e1rbara (Ponta Delgada)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_skyline           = Santa Barbara (553739587).jpg\n| image_caption           = The landscape of Santa B\u00e1rabara on the slopes of the Sete Cidades massif\n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = \n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]]\n| municipality            = [[Ponta Delgada]]\n| image_map               = Locator map AZO SMG PDL Santa Barbara.svg\n| map_caption             = The location of the civil parish of Santa B\u00e1rbara in the municipality of Ponta Delgada\n| coordinates             = {{coord|37|52|28|N|25|43|34|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: fl. 1600<br>Parish: 1 April 1986\n| area_total_km2          = 8.72\n| elevation_m             = 247\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 855\n| postal_code             = 9545-321\n| area_code               = 292\n| patron                  = [[Saint Barbara|Santa B\u00e1rbara]]\n| website                 = \n<!-- | footnotes               = Geographic detail from CAOP (2010)<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.igeo.pt/produtos/cadastro/caop/download/Areas_Freg_Mun_Dist_CAOP2010.zip|title=Carta Administrativa Oficial de Portugal|publisher=Instituto Geogr\u00e1fico Portugu\u00eas|location=Lisbon, Portugal|language=Portuguese|accessdate=1 July 2011|year=2010|editor=IGP}}</ref> produced by Instituto Geogr\u00e1fico Portugu\u00eas (IGP) -->\n}}\n'''Santa B\u00e1rbara''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the [[concelho|municipality]] of [[Ponta Delgada (Azores)|Ponta Delgada]] on the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] island of [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 855,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 8.72&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> Santa Barbara is a relatively young administrative entity, established in 1986, being de-annexed from the neighboring parish of [[Santo Ant\u00f3nio (Ponta Delgada)|Santo Ant\u00f3nio]].\n\n==Geography==\nSanta B\u00e1rbara is sandwiched between [[Santo Ant\u00f3nio (Ponta Delgada)|Santo Ant\u00f3nio]] (along the east and south), [[Rem\u00e9dios]] in the northwest, [[Sete Cidades (Ponta Delgada)|Sete Cidades]] to the southwest, and the Atlantic Ocean to the north. It is located in the northwestern part of the island of [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]]. Apart from its church (to the invocation of Santa B\u00e1rbara), along with a few small commercial businesses, there is a restaurant and a local soccer field.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santa Barbara (Ponta Delgada)}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Ponta Delgada]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_skyline           = Santa Barbara (553739587).jpg\n| image_caption           = The landscape of Santa B\u00e1rabara on the slopes of the Sete Cidades massif\n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = \n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]]\n| municipality            = [[Ponta Delgada]]\n| image_map               = Locator map AZO SMG PDL Santa Barbara.svg\n| map_caption             = The location of the civil parish of Santa B\u00e1rbara in the municipality of Ponta Delgada\n| coordinates             = {{coord|37|52|28|N|25|43|34|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: fl. 1600<br>Parish: 1 April 1986\n| area_total_km2          = 8.72\n| elevation_m             = 247\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 855\n| postal_code             = 9545-321\n| area_code               = 292\n| patron                  = [[Saint Barbara|Santa B\u00e1rbara]]\n| website                 = \n<!-- | footnotes               = Geographic detail from CAOP (2010)<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.igeo.pt/produtos/cadastro/caop/download/Areas_Freg_Mun_Dist_CAOP2010.zip|title=Carta Administrativa Oficial de Portugal|publisher=Instituto Geogr\u00e1fico Portugu\u00eas|location=Lisbon, Portugal|language=Portuguese|accessdate=1 July 2011|year=2010|editor=IGP}}</ref> produced by Instituto Geogr\u00e1fico Portugu\u00eas (IGP) -->\n}}\n'''Santa B\u00e1rbara''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the [[concelho|municipality]] of [[Ponta Delgada (Azores)|Ponta Delgada]] on the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] island of [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 855,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 8.72&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> Santa Barbara is a relatively young administrative entity, established in 1986, being de-annexed from the neighboring parish of [[Santo Ant\u00f3nio (Ponta Delgada)|Santo Ant\u00f3nio]].\n\n==Geography==\nSanta B\u00e1rbara is sandwiched between [[Santo Ant\u00f3nio (Ponta Delgada)|Santo Ant\u00f3nio]] (along the east and south), [[Rem\u00e9dios]] in the northwest, [[Sete Cidades (Ponta Delgada)|Sete Cidades]] to the southwest, and the Atlantic Ocean to the north. It is located in the northwestern part of the island of [[S\u00e3o Miguel Island|S\u00e3o Miguel]]. Apart from its church (to the invocation of Santa B\u00e1rbara), along with a few small commercial businesses, there is a restaurant and a local soccer field.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santa Barbara (Ponta Delgada)}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Ponta Delgada]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_B%C3%A1rbara_(Ponta_Delgada)"}
{"title_page": "Santa B\u00e1rbara (Angra do Hero\u00edsmo)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_skyline           = Vista da Serra de Santa B\u00e1rbara, ilha Terceira, A\u00e7ores, Portugal.jpg\n| image_caption           = The forested vista as seen from the Serra da Santa B\u00e1rbara\n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = AGH-sbarbara.png\n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[Terceira Island|Terceira]]\n| municipality            = [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n| coordinates             = {{coord|38|41|49|N|27|20|33|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: fl. 1489\n| area_total_km2          = 16.40\n| elevation_m             = 172\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 1274\n| postal_code             = 9700-471\n| area_code               = 292 \n| patron                  = [[Saint Barbara|Santa B\u00e1rbara]]\n| website                 = \n}}\n'''Santa B\u00e1rbara''' is a parish in the municipality of [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]] on the island of [[Terceira Island|Terceira]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 1,274,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of {{convert|16.40|km\u00b2|2|abbr=on}}.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> It contains the localities As Nove, Canada da Nossa Senhora da Ajuda, Pico das Seis, Pico dos Enos and Santa B\u00e1rbara.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Angra do Hero\u00edsmo}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santa Barbara (Angra do Heroismo)}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                   